\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182022\/purple-color-wall-combination-with-white-and-red.jpg\" alt=\"Purple wall colour combination with red and white accent furniture and lamps in the minimalist living room looks chic.\" class=\"wp-image-22970\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182022\/purple-color-wall-combination-with-white-and-red.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182022\/purple-color-wall-combination-with-white-and-red-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182022\/purple-color-wall-combination-with-white-and-red-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182022\/purple-color-wall-combination-with-white-and-red-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A spacious, minimalist living room  design with a purple and white colour scheme<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Magenta and White Color Scheme In Open Living Room<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can go with the purplish shades like magenta \u2014 a reddish-purple \u2014 if you are not entirely a purple fan. This open living room with a dining nook displays an elegant combination of magenta and white colour schemes. Besides the accent wall, magenta or reddish-purple is also used in different design elements like the sofa, lamp, dining nook\u2019s carpet, pendant light, etc. The magenta colour imbues a universal love vibe that is always positive to have at home.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181953\/magento-purple-wall-color-combination.jpg\" alt=\"Captivating white and purple wall color combination with coordinating furniture and lighting in living-dining space\" class=\"wp-image-22966\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181953\/magento-purple-wall-color-combination.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181953\/magento-purple-wall-color-combination-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181953\/magento-purple-wall-color-combination-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181953\/magento-purple-wall-color-combination-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A magenta colour scheme living room with an open dining area<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Mingle Purple With Orange To Create A Unique Combination<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This room has purple as the main colour scheme with a white ceiling. The purple wall colour combination is tweaked with lively orange colour dashes to create a textbook fairytale appearance. The orange curtains in the purple wall window complete the look. Then there\u2019s a mid-century style chaise lounge sofa with an orange floral print that adds a periodic, country-side appeal to the room. An old-school orange floor shade lamp accentuates it. This room creates interesting orange and purple wall combinations that are rare but gorgeous.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182042\/purple-wall-color-combination-with-organe-accent.jpg\" alt=\"Traditional living room has a purple wall color combination with an orange accent curtain and floor lamp.\" class=\"wp-image-22973\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182042\/purple-wall-color-combination-with-organe-accent.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182042\/purple-wall-color-combination-with-organe-accent-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182042\/purple-wall-color-combination-with-organe-accent-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24182042\/purple-wall-color-combination-with-organe-accent-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A traditional living room design with a periodic style couch and orange and purple colour combinations<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">And Maybe You Can Paint It All Purple?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the ultimate purple love! The room exhibits an all-purple design that could have easily fallen flat but instead manages to be stunning! Usually, using one colour scheme and that too purple for an entire room can be risky. However, if you see this set-up, you would notice how the designers have used different purple layers and combined them to give a purple room that is not too loud. It uses deeper purple shades in the ceiling and furniture sets, while a lighter purple colour creates an accent effect at the seating area\u2019s background. Purple is also used in the flooring as a carpeting design element. The room exhibits hints of white colour that blend perfectly with the all-purple look.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181941\/all-purple-color-wall-combination.jpg\" alt=\"Purple wall colour combination with L-shaped purple sofa and shelves makes a bold statement in this living room.\" class=\"wp-image-22964\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181941\/all-purple-color-wall-combination.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181941\/all-purple-color-wall-combination-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/06\/24181941\